The paper introduces a quantum programming language that extends a classical programming language, which suggests it belongs to the programming languages (cs.PL) category. The paper focuses on quantum circuits and their manipulation, which suggests it belongs to the quantum computing (cs.QU) category. The paper also discusses the operational semantics and type system of the language, which suggests it belongs to the logic in computer science (cs.LO) category. The paper proves fundamental properties of the system, which suggests it belongs to the theoretical computer science (cs.THEORY) category. Finally, the paper provides examples of circuit encoding, which suggests it belongs to the software engineering (cs.SE) category.
